genresAdvancedInfo.name: tajik pop
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Tajik pop is a genre of music that originated in Tajikistan and is popular throughout Central Asia. It is characterized by its use of synthesizers, drum machines, and other electronic instruments, and often features lyrics that address love, romance, and other popular themes. Some of the most popular Tajik pop artists include Manizha Davlatova, Shabnam Surayo, and Dilshod Rahmonov.
